        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 5:18PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles east of Whitehall to 15 miles southeast
of Harrison to 16 miles southeast of Ennis. Movement was northeast at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bozeman, Belgrade, Three Forks, Manhattan, Toston, Harrison, Big Sky,
Bozeman Hot Springs, Gallatin Gateway, Missouri Headwaters State
Park, Cardwell, Logan, Radersburg, Lewis And Clark Caverns State
Park, Maudlow, Four Corners, Amsterdam, Trident, Church Hill, and
Willow Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
